snippet.textDisplay:
number one trending and she definitely deserves it. especially since it's the original recording and not changed. I have gone through my fair share of depression issues and almost committed suicide twice, and because of my own mother no less (she told me when I moved out for my own mental health that I was stupid and never amount to anything - exact words). I still feel alone sometimes even with all the people who care. I have listened to this song about a 100 times already on repeat and I always will feel like I want to start crying because I can relate to this so much.

whoever who is going through this, please know that you are loved. there are so many helpful options out there. I can't tell you if everything is going to be okay, because I myself hate when people tell me that, but I know it's at least going to get better with the right people around you.
